The paper deals with capacity-achieving signaling strategies for the Gaussian wiretap MIMO channel, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses transmission techniques and optimization, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper considers the case of a weak eavesdropper, which is related to network security (cs.NI).
